---
import { personal } from '../data/resume';
---

<section id="about" class="px-6 py-24">
  <div class="animate-on-scroll mx-auto max-w-4xl">
    <h2 class="mb-2 text-sm font-medium tracking-widest text-accent uppercase">
      About
    </h2>
    <h3 class="mb-8 text-3xl font-bold md:text-4xl">Who I Am</h3>

    <div class="space-y-4 text-lg leading-relaxed text-text-muted">
      <p>
        I'm Prashant — a backend engineer who gets unreasonably excited about
        shaving milliseconds off query latency and automating things that used
        to take weeks.
      </p>
      <p>
        Currently at <span class="text-accent font-medium"
          >{personal.company}</span
        >, I work on the Order Management System that processes bookings across
        Expedia's global platform. My recent highlight: building an AI-assisted
        automation system that turned a
        <span class="text-text font-medium"
          >15-day manual cluster upgrade into a 15-minute</span
        > push-button operation.
      </p>
      <p>
        Before Expedia, I spent three years at
        <span class="text-text font-medium">MakeMyTrip</span> building
        microservices that saved crores in daily rebooking costs and unified
        booking engines across MMT and GoIbibo. I started my career at
        <span class="text-text font-medium">Surewaves MediaTech</span>, where I
        learned to love correlation IDs, clean schema design, and the art of
        making systems observable.
      </p>
      <p>
        Outside of code, I'm a marathon runner (5K to full), a former robotics
        competitor (Runner-Up at
        <span class="text-text font-medium">IIT Bombay's E-Yantra</span>), and
        someone who believes the best engineering is invisible to the user.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
